👥 ARC Functional Personas
1. The Operational User (Logger)
Role Scope: Real-time data entry and shift-start adjustments.

Workflow Requirements:

High-Speed Search: Must be able to query EmployeeID with minimal keystrokes.

Conditional Logic: If ID is missing, must be prompted to Add New Employee immediately.

Input Validation: Mandatory Recorded By field and Confirmation Modal before the database commit.

Data Access: Read-Only access to historical notes. No ability to delete or modify existing records within the UI.

2. The Data Administrator (IT/Admin)
Role Scope: System maintenance, data integrity, and error correction.

Workflow Requirements:

Database Management: Accesses the SQLite .db file directly via external tools for record correction/voiding.

Roster Management: Can perform bulk imports of employee lists (CSV/Excel) to keep the "Search" function accurate.

Backend Oversight: Responsible for monitoring the error_log.txt generated by the application.

3. The Analytical User (Reporting)
Role Scope: Trend analysis and staffing oversight.

Workflow Requirements:

Aggregation: Requires the "Top 10 High-Frequency" view to identify volume trends.

Audit Capability: Needs to pull a full "Individual Audit" for specific IDs to see long-term patterns.

Data Export: (Optional for MVP) Ability to copy or export report data for shift-handover emails.